columns.name: DATA AS OF
columns.description: Last date that the date was updated

columns.name: DEVELOPMENT
columns.description: The name of the housing development as listed in the Property Directory Database.

columns.name: HUD AMP#
columns.description: The U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD) identification number.

columns.name: TDS#
columns.description: Tenant Data System # - The number used by numerous computer applications to identify NYCHA Developments.

columns.name: CONSOLIDATED TDS#
columns.description: Abbreviation for Consolidated Tenant Data System Numbers. (see TDS)

columns.name: DEVELOPMENT EDP#
columns.description: Electronic Data Processing # - Number used to identify individual NYCHA developments.

columns.name: OPERATING EDP#
columns.description: Electronic Data Processing # - This number is used to identify the managing development in the consolidation.

columns.name: HUD #
columns.description: The U.S. Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD) identification number.

columns.name: PROGRAM
columns.description: The development’s funding source including Federal, Mixed Finance, or Section 8 Housing Assistance Payment (HAP) agreement.

columns.name: METHOD
columns.description:
Conventional Method:
The Authority acquires the land and contracts for general construction, heating and ventilation, elevators, electrical, and plumbing work.

Turnkey Method:
The developer buys the land, constructs the development and sells it to the Au

columns.name: TYPE
columns.description: New Construction, Rehabilitation, New Construction or Rehabilitation for the Elderly.

columns.name: NUMBER OF SECTION 8 TRANSITION APARTMENTS
columns.description: The total number of apartments transitioned to the Section 8 Program in the LLC1 and LLC2 developments.

columns.name: NUMBER OF CURRENT APARTMENTS
columns.description:
The number of apartments available for occupancy in the development as per the January 1, 2012. Dwelling Unit Inventory which is used to track
the number of apartments on the rent roll. Units temporarily vacant and not permanently removed from the rent ro

columns.name: TOTAL NUMBER OF APARTMENTS
columns.description: The total number of apartments at the development including the Section 8 Transition apartments at the LLC1 and LLC2 developments.

columns.name: NUMBER OF RENTAL ROOMS
columns.description: Rental room count per apartment is equal to 2 ½ plus the number of bedrooms. The number of rental rooms includes balconies and half-baths as half-rooms.

columns.name: AVG NO R/R PER APARTMENT
columns.description:
The average number of rental rooms per apartment is the number of rental rooms divided by the number of current apartments. The
Section 8 Apartments in the LLC1 & LLC2 Developments are included.

columns.name: POPULATION SECTION 8 TRANSITION
columns.description:
The number of persons living in the Section 8 Transition apartments in the LLC1 and LLC2 developments based on the January 1, 2012
Resident Data Files.

columns.name: POPULATION PUBLIC HOUSING
columns.description:
The number of persons living in the public housing units in the LLC1 and LLC2 developments based on the January 1, 2012 Resident Data Files.
The residents living in the Section 8 Transition apartments in the LLC1and LLC2 developments are not included in t

columns.name: TOTAL POPULATION
columns.description:
The total number of persons living at the development based on the January 1, 2012 Resident Data Files including the Section 8 Transition
apartments in the LLC1 and LLC2 developments.

columns.name: TOTAL # OF FIXED INCOME HOUSEHOLD
columns.description: Total number of families on fixed income. Fixed income is defined as households with income from Social Security, Supplementary Security Income (SSI), Survivors Insurance, Veterans Benefits, or Pension (as well as other Public or Non Public Benefits), while not earning employment income or receiving Public Assistance.

columns.name: PERCENT FIXED INCOME HOUSEHOLDS
columns.description: Total number of families on fixed income divided by the total number of families

columns.name: NUMBER OF RESIDENTIAL BLDGS
columns.description: The number of residential buildings on the grounds that are used for dwelling units.

columns.name: NUMBER OF NON-RESIDENTIAL BLDGS
columns.description: The number of non-residential buildings at a development.

columns.name: NUMBER OF STAIRHALLS
columns.description: The number of individual entrances in each Development.

columns.name: NUMBER OF STORIES
columns.description: The number of floors in each building.

columns.name: TOTAL AREA SQ FT
columns.description:
This number includes land acquired and developed as part of the development for a park or playground to be operated and maintained by the
NYC Department of Parks. At State and City Developments, the park or playground is owned by the City of New York. At

columns.name: ACRES
columns.description: The land area of the development including buildings and grounds is shown in acres (one acre equals 43,560 square feet).

columns.name: NET DEV AREA SQ FT
columns.description:
This is square feet at a development less the land set aside for a park or playground. For the majority of developments this figure is the same
acreage.

columns.name: EXCLUDING PARK ACRES
columns.description:
This is the number of acres at a development less the land set aside for a park or playground. For the majority of developments this figure is the
same as “acres”.

columns.name: BLDG COVERAGE SQ FT
columns.description: The total ground floor area of the building footprints of a development.

columns.name: CUBAGE CU FT
columns.description: Cubic Space (height x length x width of residential buildings) in all the buildings at a development, expressed as cubic feet.

columns.name: BLDG COVERAGE %
columns.description: This is the building coverage, divided by a development’s total area in square feet. This figure is presented as a percentage.

columns.name: DENSITY
columns.description: Measure of development density as represented by the number of persons per acre.

columns.name: DEVELOPMENT COST
columns.description:
The sum of the land cost, construction cost and site improvement cost, including fees for architects and engineers at the time of
original construction.

columns.name: PER RENTAL ROOM
columns.description: Cost to develop the property divided by the number of rental rooms at the time of original construction.

columns.name: AVG MONTHLY GROSS RENT
columns.description:
This is the average gross monthly rent of the households in each development as of January 1, 2012. The average tenant share of rent for the
Section 8 households in the LLC1 & LLC2 Developments is included.

columns.name: LOCATION STREET A
columns.description:
For NYCHA developments that fit into a relatively neat rectangular block or two, these fields should be the four
border streets (north, south, east and west) of the Development. For developments that are spread over some distance such as West Farms
Road R

columns.name: LOCATION STREET B
columns.description:
For NYCHA developments that fit into a relatively neat rectangular block or two, these fields should be the four
border streets (north, south, east and west) of the Development. For developments that are spread over some distance such as West Farms
Road R

columns.name: LOCATION STREET C
columns.description:
For NYCHA developments that fit into a relatively neat rectangular block or two, these fields should be the four
border streets (north, south, east and west) of the Development. For developments that are spread over some distance such as West Farms
Road R

columns.name: LOCATION STREET D
columns.description:
For NYCHA developments that fit into a relatively neat rectangular block or two, these fields should be the four
border streets (north, south, east and west) of the Development. For developments that are spread over some distance such as West Farms
Road R

columns.name: BOROUGH
columns.description: Bronx, Brooklyn, Manhattan, Queens, or Staten Island.

columns.name: COMMUNITY DISTIRCT
columns.description: Community District Number

columns.name: US CONGRESSIONAL DISTRICT
columns.description: Congressional District Number

columns.name: NY STATE SENATE DISTRICT
columns.description: New York State Senate District Number

columns.name: NY STATE ASSEMBLY DISTRICT
columns.description: New York State Assembly District Number

columns.name: NY CITY COUNCIL DISTRICT
columns.description: New York City Council District Number

columns.name: COMPLETION DATE
columns.description: The Initial Occupancy Completion Date: The date when the development was at least 95% occupied.

columns.name: FEDERALIZED DEVELOPMENT
columns.description:
A development transferred from the City or State Program. The book has a list of developments that were transferred after construction was
completed from either the City or State Program to the Federal Program. These developments are managed and operated

columns.name: SENIOR DEVELOPMENT
columns.description:
A senior development where all residents are senior, aged 62 or older, is denoted as "Exclusively". A development where only some buildings
are designated for senior residents is denoted as "Partially". A list of these developments is also included on pag

columns.name: ELECTRICITY PAID BY RESIDENTS
columns.description: A "Yes" indicates developments where residents pay for their electricity.

columns.name: PRIVATE MANAGEMENT
columns.description:
A "Yes" indicates Developments managed by a private management company. A list of these developments is also included on page 133 of this
book.

view.description: Contains the main body of the “Development Data Book” as of January 1, 2019. The Development Data Book lists all of the Authority's Developments alphabetically and includes information on the development identification numbers, program and construction type, number of apartments and rental rooms, population, number of buildings and stories, street boundaries, and political districts.
